## How it works
Workflow runs triggered by a contributor's pull request from a fork do not automatically receive access to repository secrets or privileged runner contexts. ...
> **Warning**: The `pull_request_target` event runs in the base repository context and CAN access secrets. Do not use `pull_request_target` with untrusted code from forks unless the workflow has been thoroughly reviewed and secret exposure is limited.
...
## Checklist for reviewers
- [ ] Inspect `.github/workflows/` for new or modified steps.
- [ ] Confirm no new steps request repository secrets unnecessarily.
- [ ] Check for changes to self-hosted runner configuration or commands that fetch external scripts.
- [ ] If unsure, re-run tests in an internal branch or request changes instead of approving.
...
```
